4
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:48,640
Hello?

5
00:01:49,390 --> 00:01:51,050
Is it the automobile 4S store?

6
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:53,729
My car

7
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,380
is powering off,

8
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:59,100
so I have to park it by the roadside.

9
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:00,960
Can send someone to help me?

10
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:07,400
I'm at Jingwang East Road，

11
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:08,889
around the intersection.

12
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:15,610
Righteous Luo.

13
00:02:16,650 --> 00:02:17,770
What do you want?

14
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,380
Where are you?

15
00:02:21,380 --> 00:02:23,360
Does it matter to you?

16
00:02:23,670 --> 00:02:24,710
Of course it does.

17
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:26,030
I represent the bank.

18
00:02:26,060 --> 00:02:28,190
I want to meet you and discuss the case.

19
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:29,460
Seriously? Unscrupulous Chen,

20
00:02:29,460 --> 00:02:31,120
is it the way you practice law?

21
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:32,250
You represent the plaintiff,

22
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:34,710
but you discuss the case with the defendant.

23
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:36,100
Does the law forbid lawyers from contacting

24
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:38,360
the clients of their opposing counsels?

25
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:40,829
Fine. I happen to need a life coach.

26
00:02:41,230 --> 00:02:42,430
Come and meet me then.

27
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,300
Zhang Shilan, give me my bag.

28
00:02:45,380 --> 00:02:46,450
Where are you going? I'll go with you.

29
00:02:46,450 --> 00:02:48,160
I'm meeting with a client. Give it to me.

30
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,270
What... What about me?

31
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:51,470
Get yourself a ride back to the law firm.

32
00:03:16,350 --> 00:03:17,280
-Hello.
-Hello.

33
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:18,590
Is this your car?

34
00:03:18,690 --> 00:03:19,770
Yes. My car...

35
00:03:20,070 --> 00:03:20,660
Has it powered off?

36
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:21,110
Yes.

37
00:03:21,230 --> 00:03:22,430
Okay. First thing first,

38
00:03:22,430 --> 00:03:23,490
we'll charge a fee for towing the car away.

39
00:03:23,490 --> 00:03:24,020
Okay.

40
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:24,870
Wait!

41
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,960
I'm a VIP customer.

42
00:03:26,990 --> 00:03:28,100
Do I need to pay for that?

43
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,700
I'm afraid so. It's our rule.

44
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,920
Okay, here's the key.

45
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:35,860
-Don't forget to put the tripod away.
-Okay. Consider it done.

46
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,400
Be careful when you tow it away.

47
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,320
Thank you, sir.

48
00:03:40,350 --> 00:03:40,740
No problem.

49
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:42,050
What happened? Has your car powered off?

50
00:03:42,050 --> 00:03:44,250
It's none of your business. Just drive.

51
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:53,370
Where are we going?

52
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,070
I've driven for a while but you haven't told me a destination.

53
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:02,490
Do you have a problem with that?

54
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:06,450
You're driving a luxury car. Don't tell me you're gonna skimp on the gas.

55
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:07,350
Just stop asking me questions.

56
00:04:07,350 --> 00:04:08,060
Keep driving.

57
00:04:08,060 --> 00:04:10,260
I'll tell you when we need to make a turn.

58
00:04:12,890 --> 00:04:13,620
Now spill it.

59
00:04:13,650 --> 00:04:15,180
What do you want to teach me?

60
00:04:16,149 --> 00:04:18,339
Why did you appeal at the last moment?

61
00:04:18,589 --> 00:04:19,579
You're funny.

62
00:04:19,829 --> 00:04:21,380
I'm entitled to file an appeal within the statutory time limit.

63
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:22,390
Whenever I feel like doing so,

64
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,470
I go with it.

65
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,150
What? Does it bother you?

66
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:28,930
Turn right.

67
00:04:30,030 --> 00:04:31,020
Okay.

68
00:04:31,050 --> 00:04:32,260
Turn right.

69
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,710
Listen.

70
00:04:44,730 --> 00:04:46,280
I have no doubt that you'll lose

71
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,350
when you're up against me in court.

72
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:48,710
However, I do have doubts,

73
00:04:48,710 --> 00:04:49,909
if you go down without a fight.

74
00:04:49,909 --> 00:04:51,610
I don't believe there isn't a trick up your sleeve.

75
00:04:51,610 --> 00:04:53,420
Take it down a notch, braggart.

76
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:56,560
Didn't you lose to me in a previous case?

77
00:04:56,590 --> 00:04:58,120
Try doing my job, I dare you.

78
00:04:58,230 --> 00:05:00,030
I was supposed to get my client off a charge of sexual harassment.

79
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:01,590
But he turned out to be rapist.

80
00:05:01,590 --> 00:05:03,320
Even God couldn't help him out.

81
00:05:04,970 --> 00:05:06,570
Tell me. What's on your mind?

82
00:05:06,650 --> 00:05:07,690
Nothing.

83
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,470
I'm just bored.

84
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:11,040
I've got nothing better to do.

85
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:11,730
I happen to be in the mood of teasing you.

86
00:05:11,730 --> 00:05:12,860
That's impossible.

87
00:05:15,350 --> 00:05:16,390
Slow down.

88
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,150
Over there. Pull over.

89
00:05:20,990 --> 00:05:21,650
Okay. Okay.

90
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:22,910
Thank you.

91
00:05:23,650 --> 00:05:24,710
What is this place?

92
00:05:25,850 --> 00:05:26,910
Did you really think

93
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:28,810
I'd talk about the case with you?

94
00:05:29,150 --> 00:05:30,200
My car broke down.

95
00:05:30,470 --> 00:05:32,380
I was using you as my chauffeur.

96
00:05:34,990 --> 00:05:35,720
I'm leaving.

97
00:05:35,790 --> 00:05:36,460
Thank you.

98
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,240
Hold on!

99
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:41,150
Is this a cosmetics store?

100
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:41,770
Yes.

101
00:05:41,990 --> 00:05:43,430
Are you buying cosmetics?

102
00:05:43,430 --> 00:05:44,090
Oh. Come on.

103
00:05:44,390 --> 00:05:47,790
Can't a woman shop for cosmetics?

104
00:05:47,909 --> 00:05:48,909
Are you okay?

105
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,850
I'm leaving. Bye.

106
00:05:57,409 --> 00:05:58,940
She fooled me again.

107
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,810
Bye. We look forward to your next purchase.

108
00:06:12,810 --> 00:06:15,130
Hello, I wanna ask you about a person.

109
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:16,340
There used to be

110
00:06:16,470 --> 00:06:17,740
an employee in your store

111
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:19,400
named Wen Li. Do you remember?

112
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:20,830
Wen Li?

113
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:22,820
We don't know her.

114
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:27,150
Just a second. I have her photo.

115
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,650
Do you remember her?

116
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:31,880
Isn't it Ms. Wen?

117
00:06:31,910 --> 00:06:32,390
Yeah.

118
00:06:32,390 --> 00:06:33,909
Her name isn't Wen Li.

119
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,700
What do you call her then?

120
00:06:35,890 --> 00:06:36,860
Wen Rong.

121
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:38,590
She worked here before.

122
00:06:38,590 --> 00:06:40,320
But she left after a few months.

123
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:42,830
Who was she familiar with

124
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,320
when she was working here?

125
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,310
Ms. Li.

126
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,970
A customer would like to ask you about Ms. Wen.

127
00:06:49,070 --> 00:06:49,670
Ms. Wen?

128
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,070
Yes.

129
00:06:50,450 --> 00:06:51,210
Hello.

130
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:52,460
You can call me Ms. Luo.

131
00:06:52,460 --> 00:06:53,940
This is my business card.

132
00:07:02,910 --> 00:07:03,790
Hello, sir.

133
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,280
How can I help you?

134
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,000
A woman in shorts

135
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,720
got in here, right?

136
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:10,400
Did she buy anything?

137
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,480
Nothing.

138
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:12,880
She came to ask about

139
00:07:12,910 --> 00:07:14,660
a girl who worked here before.

140
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,790
She came to ask about a girl then.

141
00:07:17,790 --> 00:07:18,910
Who's that girl?

142
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,150
When that girl was working here,

143
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:22,580
she went by the name of Wen Rong.

144
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:25,040
For some reason, this lady calls her Wen Li.

145
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,050
I don't think you should ask more questions.

146
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:30,110
We're not supposed to disclose customer information.

147
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,650
Wen Li is my younger sister.

148
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:34,750
Why would this lady ask about her?

149
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:37,250
Who... Who is this lady then?

150
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:40,550
She's my girlfriend.

151
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:42,350
We're getting married soon.

152
00:07:42,350 --> 00:07:44,550
She goes around, asking everyone about me.

153
00:07:44,550 --> 00:07:45,120
Really?

154
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:47,480
Maybe she just wants to know more about me.

155
00:07:47,590 --> 00:07:48,710
I suggest

156
00:07:48,909 --> 00:07:50,770
you should be careful around her.

157
00:07:50,909 --> 00:07:52,030
I really should.

158
00:07:52,590 --> 00:07:53,350
Okay, I got it.

159
00:07:53,350 --> 00:07:53,990
Thank you.

160
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,310
I'll take this.

161
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:58,120
-Okay. I’ll get you the bill.
-Okay.

162
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:58,720
Thank you.

163
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:25,990
Wen Li...

164
00:08:27,470 --> 00:08:28,830
Who is this woman?

165
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,950
Is she relevant to the case about the bank?

166
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:35,950
Do you mean that she seduced another woman's husband?

167
00:08:36,570 --> 00:08:36,990
Yes.

168
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,370
She colluded with my client's husband

169
00:08:40,710 --> 00:08:41,730
to transfer all the property

170
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,860
that my client owned with her husband.

171
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:45,430
What else

172
00:08:45,430 --> 00:08:46,950
do you know

173
00:08:46,970 --> 00:08:48,200
about her?

174
00:08:51,110 --> 00:08:53,360
Now that you've spoken of it,

175
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:54,890
I remember

176
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:57,030
how I felt about her.

177
00:08:57,230 --> 00:08:58,630
She seemed

178
00:08:58,710 --> 00:08:59,830
quite gentle

179
00:09:00,230 --> 00:09:01,230
and

180
00:09:01,230 --> 00:09:02,560
she was a smooth talker.

181
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:04,400
She's smart at work.

182
00:09:04,740 --> 00:09:07,500
But she appeared to be quite introverted.

183
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:09,680
Several senior employees

184
00:09:09,710 --> 00:09:11,160
took advantage of her

185
00:09:11,180 --> 00:09:13,950
and made her do the most tiring chores.

186
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:16,020
She never fought back.

187
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:18,310
Instead, she lapped up the entire workload.

188
00:09:18,310 --> 00:09:19,840
Sometimes

189
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:21,110
I felt sorry for her,

190
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:22,430
so I helped her.

191
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:23,470
At that time,

192
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:26,110
Ms. Wen was such a poor girl.

193
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:27,530
Look,

194
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:29,310
she couldn't make much money from her job.

195
00:09:29,310 --> 00:09:30,590
She had to use the most part of her salary

196
00:09:30,590 --> 00:09:31,920
to pay her monthly rent.

197
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:33,650
On occasion, she couldn't afford her rent.

198
00:09:33,650 --> 00:09:35,250
So her landlord evicted her.

199
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:37,130
She would sneak back

200
00:09:37,590 --> 00:09:38,920
and sleep in our office.

201
00:09:39,060 --> 00:09:40,710
I felt like I had to do something.

202
00:09:40,710 --> 00:09:41,990
I sympathized her.

203
00:09:42,340 --> 00:09:44,060
So I let her stay at my place.

204
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:45,860
However,

205
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:48,210
something happened at that time.

206
00:09:48,580 --> 00:09:51,110
My husband is a college teacher.

207
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:53,980
Maybe I misread his interaction with Ms. Wen.

208
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:56,260
Ms. Wen seemed to be extra nice

209
00:09:56,710 --> 00:09:58,370
to my husband, behind my back.

210
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:00,250
Later on, she figured out

211
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:01,980
that I was wary of her,

212
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:03,900
so she moved out soon.

213
00:10:07,620 --> 00:10:10,480
She knew she had aroused your suspicion, so she left. Right?

214
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,110
Did anything else happen?

215
00:10:12,130 --> 00:10:13,270
Please try to think about it.

216
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:16,860
Maybe Wang Liang was the reason for her departure.

217
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:20,040
That young man used to take his girlfriend

218
00:10:20,070 --> 00:10:21,950
to buy cosmetics in our store.

219
00:10:22,230 --> 00:10:23,350
There's gonna be a huge discount.

220
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:24,730
Plus this eye cream, the total will be 3,000, right?

221
00:10:24,730 --> 00:10:25,160
Yes.

222
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:27,820
We'll give you two samples as well.

223
00:10:27,820 --> 00:10:28,620
Wang Liang.

224
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:29,880
It's gonna be 3,000.

225
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:32,330
It's okay. We'll buy whatever you like.

226
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,500
I'll take this 3,000-worth makeup kit then.

227
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:37,970
Get off your phone.

228
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:43,090
We have some new facial masks over there.

229
00:10:43,090 --> 00:10:44,350
Why not browse around?

230
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:46,040
Sounds great.

231
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,630
Before I knew it,

232
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:49,830
that young man had become close to Ms. Wen.

233
00:10:49,830 --> 00:10:51,350
He even came to my house to meet her.

234
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:53,350
I saw that happen once.

235
00:10:53,710 --> 00:10:56,020
Ms. Wen was very embarrassed.

236
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:58,410
She said that man wasn't the one I knew of.

237
00:10:58,470 --> 00:11:00,510
Since then,

238
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:01,510
she disappeared.

239
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:02,920
Wang Liang

240
00:11:02,950 --> 00:11:05,190
then became Wen Li's boyfriend.

241
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:08,670
Thanks to him, Wen Li was able to register

242
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:11,070
as a permanent resident in Jingbei.

243
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:12,900
Then she dumped Wang Liang.

244
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:14,710
Gosh!

245
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:15,590
Is this...

246
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:18,480
Is this real?

247
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:19,710
It seems...

248
00:11:19,990 --> 00:11:22,120
I didn't expect her to be such a person.

249
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:25,230
If she is a terrible person

250
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:26,350
like you have described,

251
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:27,430
wouldn't she

252
00:11:27,470 --> 00:11:29,990
take revenge on those senior employees

253
00:11:30,010 --> 00:11:31,750
who used to  bully her in the store?

254
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:32,990
She just left

255
00:11:32,990 --> 00:11:34,630
and never declared to take vengeance.

256
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:36,490
That's because she didn't care about

257
00:11:36,490 --> 00:11:37,280
those girls.

258
00:11:37,710 --> 00:11:39,170
She is very ambitious.

259
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:41,240
She's got a bigger goal than that.

260
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:44,820
This...

261
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,440
This is really...

262
00:11:47,050 --> 00:11:48,300
scary.

263
00:11:48,850 --> 00:11:50,650
Don't you know what courtesy is?

264
00:11:51,170 --> 00:11:52,990
Do you think you can get your way around?

265
00:11:52,990 --> 00:11:55,320
Haven't your mother taught you anything?

266
00:11:55,860 --> 00:11:57,220
I'm sorry. Sorry.

267
00:11:58,450 --> 00:11:59,980
Are you gonna cry over this?

268
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,730
What do think you are doing?

269
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:05,540
Have I done anything to you?

270
00:12:05,770 --> 00:12:07,650
Turn off the waterworks!

271
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:09,760
I'm not buying any of this!

272
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:11,040
It won't work here.

273
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,020
What did I say?

274
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,070
Did I hurt her or what?

275
00:12:13,070 --> 00:12:14,910
Have I done anything to make you cry?

276
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,390
What do you mean by this?

277
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:21,080
Listen up. Your little stunt won't work.

278
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:23,210
You'll either do your job or just quit.

279
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:27,440
Come on in, Ms. Luo.

280
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,000
Have a seat.

281
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:31,400
I’ll get you some water.

282
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:34,290
Wang Liang.

283
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,110
What a coincidence!

284
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:37,820
You said you wanted to see me.

285
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:39,350
I was also gonna ask you for a meeting.

